    "description": {
      "es": "",
      "en": "Compute the annotations dict for an object. obj may be a callable, class, module, or other object with __annotate__ or __annotations__ attributes. Passing any other object raises TypeError. The format parameter controls the format in which annotations are returned, and must be a member of the Format enum or its integer equivalent. The different formats work as follows: VALUE: object.__annotations__ is tried first; if that does not exist, the object.__annotate__ function is called if it exists..."
